==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[w:Slavic languages|Slavic]] suffix (Russian: [[-ик]]). This suffix experienced a surge in English coinages for nicknames and diminutives after the 1957 Russian launch of the [[w:Sputnik program|Sputnik]] spacecraft.  Carries heavy influence from {{etyl|yi}} use of -nik and similar borrowed words ([[nogoodnik]], [[nudnik]], [[kibbutznik]]).

===Suffix===
'''-nik'''

# Appended to words to create a [[nickname]] for a person who [[exemplify|exemplifies]], [[endorse]]s, or is associated with the thing or quality specified (by the base form), often a particular [[ideology]] or preference.

